cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.SE, cs.DS

This paper deals with the algebraic characterization of concurrent composition, which is a topic related to programming languages (cs.PL) and formal languages (cs.FL). The paper also uses ideas based on automata theory (cs.LO) and synchronization (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with the concept of concurrency, which is a topic related to distributed systems (cs.DS).
